KwaZulu-Natal MEC for community safety Mxolisi Kaunda has applauded gains made by a special task team investigating political killings in the province.ADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads“We are confident that the team will bring those responsible for this dastardly deed to book and they will restore peace and stability in the province soon.” he said.On Tuesday , the task team released identikits of two men whom they believe can assist with the attempted murder of three Umzimkhulu councillors, including former ANC Youth League secretary general Sindiso Magaqa.The team has also arrested a suspect for the murder Mbhekiseni Khumalo, a ward councillor in Phongolo who was shot dead at his homestead in December.The MEC has hailed the arrest as a victory for justice and the rule of law in the province."We will not allow anarchy and lawlessness to be the order of the day in KwaZulu-Natal,” Kaunda said.The task team appealed to anyone with any information regarding the whereabouts of the men to urgently contact the investigating officer, Warrant Officer Benginkosi Jeza on 071 351 7233 or Crime Stop on 08600 10111.The Mercury